    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The kernel elements of the filter form a tent shape with increasing sides, for example:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "media-2556918",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "2556918",
                "title": "Figure 1"
              },
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Like a box filter, this arrangement allows for much faster algorithms, especially for larger blur radii but with a more pleasing appearance.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The tent blur is a separable filter and the Metal Performance Shaders framework will act accordingly to give the best performance for multi-dimensional blurs.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The box filter, while fast, may yield square-ish looking blur effects. However, multiple passes of the box filter tend to smooth out with each additional pass. For example, two 3-wide box blurs produces the same effective convolution as a 5-wide tent blur.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "In effect, addition passes tend to approximate a Gaussian line shape.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
